<TITLE> Govt decides not to hike urea price </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 19 (bdnews24.com)  The government Thursday scuttled a proposal to increase the urea fertiliser price for the time being. A meeting of the advisory committee on economic affairs made the decision in line wuith an earlier recommendation by the Ministry of Industries. The committee asked the ministries to draft a comprehensive proposal on possible price increases of gas, electricity and petroleum products. "The matter of increasing the price of fertiliser will be raised at the next meeting of the council of advisers and a decision will be taken then," finance adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam said after the meeting. "Power, energy and gas have links to the agricultural sector. After sending a coordinated proposal regarding these issues to the advisory council the price for fertilisers will be settled." On the decision on the lease purchase of an Airbus for Biman Bangladesh Airlines, the adviser said, "A decision was taken to lease the aircraft for three years at a cost of 23 million dollars after which Biman would own it." bdnews24.com/
